{
  "local_port": 38996,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should every first time anime convention goer know?",
  "response": "Attending an anime convention for the first time can be an exciting and overwhelming experience. Here are some tips to help you make the most of it:\n\n1. **Plan Ahead:** \n   - Research the convention's schedule and map to prioritize panels, events, and dealer room visits.\n   - Consider purchasing tickets in advance to avoid long lines at the venue.\n\n2. **Budget Your Spending:**\n   - Set a budget for your trip, including tickets, travel, lodging, food, and merchandise.\n   - Be mindful of impulse purchases; dealer rooms and artist alleys can be tempting!\n\n3. **Pack Essentials:**\n   - Bring comfortable clothing and shoes, as you may be walking or standing a lot.\n   - Pack a refillable water bottle and snacks to stay hydrated and energized.\n   - Consider bringing a portable charger for your phone or other electronics.\n\n4. **Respect Cosplayers and Others:**\n   - Always ask for permission before taking photos of cosplayers.\n   - Be mindful of personal space and avoid touching costumes without consent.\n\n5. **Participate in Activities:**\n   - Attend panels, workshops, and screenings that interest you.\n   - Engage in community events like cosplay contests or fan meetups.\n\n6. **Follow Convention Rules:**\n   - Be aware of the convention's policies regarding photography, behavior, and prohibited items.\n   - Listen to staff and security for guidance and instructions.\n\n7. **Stay Safe:**\n   - Keep an eye on your belongings and be cautious in crowded areas.\n   - Travel in groups when possible, especially at night.\n\n8. **Be Considerate:**\n   - Respect other attendees' enjoyment and be polite and courteous in interactions.\n   - Share space in popular areas and lines, and keep noise in check during screenings and panels.\n\n9. **Take Breaks:**\n   - Rest when needed. Conventions can be exhausting, so don\u2019t hesitate to take breaks or head back to your hotel for a moment of quiet.\n\n10. **Network and Make Friends:**\n    - Use this opportunity to meet people who share your interests. Exchange social media or contact info to stay in touch after the event.\n\nRemember, the key is to enjoy the experience, so have fun and embrace the unique culture of the anime community!",
